raw_data.title: Audio Engineer
raw_data.description: The Audio Engineer provides audio engineering support. The primary focus of this position is to organize, produce and ensure file quality and conversion for audio created as part of live or pre-recorded segments, which includes audio / video podcasts, public service announcements, live media uplinks and field audio. This position may involve travel.

raw_data.title: Sr. Post-Pay Operations Coordinator

raw_data.title: Museum Registrar Collections Manager
raw_data.description: Implements policies and procedures that relate to caring for collections. Organizes collection by donor, medium such as sculpture, artist and time period, or discipline such as archeology. Maintains records of accession, condition, and location of objects in museum collection, and oversees movement, packing, and shipping of objects to conform to insurance regulations. Observes unpacking of objects acquired by museum through gift, purchase, or loan to determine that damage or deterioration to objects has not occurred. Registers and assigns accession and catalog numbers to all objects in collection, according to established registration system. Composes concise description of objects, and records descriptions on file cards and in collection catalogs. Oversees handling, packing, movement, and inspection of all objects entering or leaving establishment, including traveling exhibits. Works with other personnel to develop and initiate practical methods of packing and shipping fragile or valuable objects. Maintains records of storage, exhibit, and loan locations of all objects in collection for establishment personnel, insurance representatives, and other persons utilizing facilities. Prepares acquisition reports for review of curatorial and administrative staff.  Periodically reviews and evaluates registration and catalog system to maintain applicability, consistency, and operation. Recommends changes in recordkeeping procedures to achieve maximum accessibility to and efficient retrieval of collection objects. Arranges for insurance of objects on loan or special exhibition or recommends insurance coverage on parts of or entire collection. Identifies and resolves educational needs of target audiences by designing and developing instructional products. Writes learner outcomes/performance objectives in specific measurable terms. Responsible for aiding in own self-development by being available and receptive to any training made available by the company. Plans daily activities within the guidelines of company policy, job description and supervisor’s instruction in such a way as to maximize personal output.
